'''Mohamed El Amine Amoura''' ({{langx|ar|محمد الأمين عمورة}}; born 9 May 2000) is an Algerian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker (association football)|striker]] for {{German football updater|Wolfsburg}} club [[VfL Wolfsburg]] and the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

== Club career ==
=== ES Setif ===
Amoura made his professional debut with [[ES Sétif]] in a 3–0 [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1]] win over [[CA Bordj Bou Arréridj]] on 17 February 2020, scoring his side's third goal after coming on as a late sub.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reporters.dz/es-setif-le-joueur-de-20-ans-creve-lecran-en-ce-debut-de-saison-amoura-prodige-detecte/|title=ES Sétif/Le joueur de 20 ans crève l'écran en ce début de saison : Amoura, prodige détecté|language=fr|first=Mohamed|last=Touileb|date=4 January 2021|publisher=Reporters.dz|access-date=17 June 2021|archive-date=21 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121172158/https://www.reporters.dz/es-setif-le-joueur-de-20-ans-creve-lecran-en-ce-debut-de-saison-amoura-prodige-detecte/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was in blistering form in the 2020–21 season, finishing with 13 goals in 25 games.

=== Lugano ===
On 29 August 2021, Amoura joined [[Swiss Super League]] club [[FC Lugano|Lugano]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ruberti |first1=Andrea |url=https://www.fclugano.com/mohammed-elamine-amoura-rinforza-lattacco-bianconero/|title=Mohammed-Elamine Amoura rinforza l'attacco bianconero|work=FC Lugano |language=it|date=29 August 2021}}</ref>

=== Union SG ===
On 17 August 2023, Amoura joined [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union SG]] on a four-year contract with an option for another season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rusg.brussels/en/news/mohamed-amoura-new-union-striker|title=Mohamed Amoura new Union striker|publisher=Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|date=17 August 2023}}</ref>

=== VfL Wolfsburg (loan) ===
On 8 July 2024, Amoura moved to [[VfL Wolfsburg]] in Germany.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=VfL Wolfsburg|url=https://www.vfl-wolfsburg.de/newsdetails/news-detail/detail/news/power-fuer-die-offensive|title=POWER FÜR DIE OFFENSIVE|trans-title=POWER FOR THE OFFENSIVE|date=8 July 2024|access-date=8 July 2024|language=de}}</ref>

== International career ==
Amoura is eligible to represent [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] (country of birth) and [[France national football team|France]] (through his parents). Amoura holds both Algerian and French nationalities from his parents.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Silas |first=Don |date=2024-09-04 |title='My mother is from France' - Amoura on why he snubbed France |url=https://dailypost.ng/2024/09/04/my-mother-is-from-france-amoura-on-why-he-snubbed-france/ |location=Lagos, Nigeria|access-date=2025-04-05 |newspaper=[[Daily Post (Nigeria)|Daily Post]]|language=en-US |archive-date=10 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240910113312/https://dailypost.ng/2024/09/04/my-mother-is-from-france-amoura-on-why-he-snubbed-france/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Amoura was called up to represent the [[Algeria A' national football team|Algeria A' national team]] for a friendly on 17 June 2021.<ref name="الخبر 2021">{{cite web | title=الخبر-التشكيلة الأساسية للمنتخب المحلي ضد ليبيريا | website=الخبر | date=17 June 2021 | url=http://elkhabar.com/press/article/188402/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B4%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%B6%D8%AF-%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7/ | language=ar | access-date=17 June 2021}}</ref> and scored four goals in a 5–1 win over [[Liberia national football team|Liberia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elbilad.net/article/detail?id=116240|language=ar|title=البلاد الرياضي / عمورة يصنع الحدث مع المنتخب الوطني المحلي|website=elbilad.net}}</ref>

That same year he was called up to the senior team.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://dzballon.com/2021/08/29/lugano-annonce-larrivee-damoura/|title=Le FC Lugano annonce l'arrivée d'Amoura|publisher=DZBallon|date=29 August 2021|language=FR}}</ref> In December 2023, he was named in Algeria's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].
On March 25, 2025, he scored his first hat-trick for the Algeria national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.algerie-focus.com/can-2024-lalgerie-devoile-sa-liste-officielle-qui-sont-les-fennecs-prets-a-conquerir-lafrique/|title=CAN 2024 : L'Algérie Dévoile sa Liste Officielle – Qui Sont les Fennecs Prêts à Conquérir l'Afrique ?|language=French|date=30 December 2023|access-date=12 January 2024|publisher=Algérie-Focus}}</ref>

